article.story: LOS ANGELES -- — Justice Hill had 23 points in Loyola Marymount's 88-66 victory against Jackson State on Tuesday. Hill added eight assists for the Lions (2-1). Dominick Harris added 18 points while going 6 of 8 (4 for 6 from 3-point range), and he also had six rebounds. Will Johnston shot 3 for 9, including 2 for 7 from beyond the arc to finish with 10 points. Ken Evans led the Tigers (0-4) in scoring, finishing with 33 points and two steals. Jordan O'Neal added 10 points for Jackson State. In addition, Coltie Young finished with five points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
